---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Support" description="Get help with Omnigram">
  <div class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-invert prose-slate">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-10">Support</h1>

      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Omnigram is an open-source project. We offer community-based support through the following channels.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">Report a Bug</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        If you've found a bug or something isn't working as expected, please open an issue on GitHub:
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/lxpio/omnigram/issues/new" target="_blank"
         class="inline-block mt-3 px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition no-underline">
        Open an Issue on GitHub
      </a>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">Community Discussions</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        For questions, feature requests, or general discussion, visit our GitHub Discussions:
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/lxpio/omnigram/discussions" target="_blank"
         class="inline-block mt-3 px-6 py-3 bg-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-600 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition no-underline">
        Join the Discussion
      </a>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">Documentation</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        For setup guides, configuration help, and usage instructions:
      </p>
      <a href="/getting-started/quick-start"
         class="inline-block mt-3 px-6 py-3 bg-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-600 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition no-underline">
        Read the Docs
      </a>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">Email Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        For security issues or private inquiries:
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        <a href="mailto:omnigram@lxpio.com" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">omnigram@lxpio.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 mt-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">How do I set up my own server?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2">
            Follow our <a href="/getting-started/installation" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Installation Guide</a>
            to deploy Omnigram on Docker with a single command.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">How do I configure AI features?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2">
            Go to Settings in the app, enter your AI provider's API key (OpenAI, Claude, Ollama, etc.).
            AI features are optional — the app works fully without them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">How do I delete my data?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2">
            Since Omnigram is self-hosted, you have full control. Uninstall the app to remove local data.
            Delete your account or remove the server instance for server-side data.
            See our <a href="/privacy#data-deletion" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Data Deletion</a> section for details.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">Which ebook formats are supported?</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2">
            EPUB is the primary supported format. PDF support is also available.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
